                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4960/77.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Yenikeny</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 48. Beferring to the fifth demand in his telegram of April 10, reports the
                    satisfactory settlement of the Manoukian case,<note n="a" xml:id="d415fna">See
                        following subject.</note> which has been so long pending, and which involved
                    the recognition by the Sublime Porte of our consular courts as alone competent
                    to decide as to legal heirs of an American citizen.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
